        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently, the array $inputFilterSpecification passed to InputFilter\\Factory::createInputFilter may only contain values that can be passed on to createInput(), which means that the values must be arrays or instances of Traversable. For this reason, the user cannot manually initialize any Inputs or sub InputFilters prior to calling createInputFilter().\r\n\r\nThe next code lines will clarify the issue.\r\n\r\nI suggest that these lines:\r\n-----\r\n{noformat} \r\nforeach ($inputFilterSpecification as $key => $value) {\r\n  $input = $this->createInput($value);\r\n  $inputFilter->add($input, $key);\r\n}\r\n{noformat} \r\n-----\r\nwould be changed with these:\r\n-----\r\n{noformat} \r\nforeach ($inputFilterSpecification as $key => $value) {\r\n  if(($value instanceof InputInterface) || ($value instanceof InputFilterInterface)){\r\n    $input = $value;\r\n  }\r\n  else{\r\n    $input = $this->createInput($value);\r\n  }\r\n  \r\n  $inputFilter->add($input, $key);\r\n}\r\n{noformat} \r\n-----\r\n\r\nI'm sending a pull request for this."
        },
